public int compare(java.lang.Object o1,
                   java.lang.Object o2)
Compares two DOM Attr objects based on their name. Names are compared using the standard String.compare function. Arguments must implement the DOM Attr interface

Specified by:
compare in interface java.util.Comparator
Parameters:
o1 - First Attr object to be compared.
o2 - Second Attr object to be compared.
Returns:
Returns a negative int, zero, or positive int if o1 is less than, equal to, or greater than o2, respectively.
